7. Better interface habits

This one is underrated.

The ChatGPT interface has gradually accumulated capabilities that are useful if you treat it like a development environment instead of only a chatbot.

Examples include:

* attaching documents for review
* generating downloadable files (like Markdown, PDFs, spreadsheets, presentations, depending on the task)
* working iteratively on longer artifacts
* searching your uploaded files when needed
* using connected tools (calendar, Gmail, etc.) for workflows where they’re appropriate

The leverage comes from choosing the right medium for the job instead of forcing everything into chat messages.

